4.75,12.6,4.5,4.5,5,5,4.5,"Heavy aromas of flowers, citrus fruit, and wild hops.  The carbonation bubbles ever so slowly float to the top of the glass.  Carries flowery notes as well as sweet malts, but the hops bitterness dominates the palate.  So smooth and creamy and filling!  A fantastic I.P.A.  Would expect no less from Stone Brewery.","Jordan","Jan 17, 2002"
4.23,0.2,4.5,4,4.5,4,4,"Notes: Wow now this is an IPA! Well attenuated and very bitter, yet still a little malt character to balance. Seriously ... if you don't like hoppy beers than this one might not be a good pick. If you are a hophead ... than buy a case! There was only one thing this beer said to me ""Don't be a whimp, drink a hoppy beer!"" Also this a quite deceiving brew topping out at 6.9% abv.","Jason","Jan 25, 2001"
